    "Name": "Annihilator",
    "Details": "The first of two variants seeking to take advantage of newly developed Clan technology, the Annihilator C was rebuilt using only Clan technology during the Golden Century and later replicated by the Wolf's Dragoons in the post-Clan Invasion era. An endo steel frame and three tons less armor than the ANH-1X allowed the Annihilator C to mount a larger engine to increased its maximum speed to 54 km/h. The 'Mech was armed with four Ultra autocannon/10s and four ER medium lasers. The Ultra autocannon/10s allowed the 'Mech to fire at twice the rate of a normal autocannon, allowing it to put as much fire out as if it was carrying eight regular autocannons.<br><br>X-class mechs feature upgrades to their armour, thermal management and defensive systems that improve their survivability on the 31st century battlefield.",
